<div class="inset-column">
<h2>What is FDA’s role in regulating drugs?</h2>

<p>We oversee prescription, generic, biosimilars, and over-the-counter drugs. But what is our role when it comes to drug regulation? </p>

<div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9"><iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" class="embed-responsive-item" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zfnhrEWuRME?si=OLhZ82ST4xWH3CkO" title="YouTube video player" width="560"></iframe></div>

<p style="margin: 1em 0px"><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="9900496d-c813-4167-ac5b-ad482bbc8938" href="/drugs/information-consumers-and-patients-drugs/transcript-what-fdas-role-regulating-drugs" title="What is FDA's Role in regulating drugs?">Transcript</a></p>

<hr /><h2>How does the FDA approve new drugs?</h2>

<p>Prescription drugs go through many steps and phases before they’re approved by us. What does this process look like from beginning to end?</p>

<div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9"><iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" class="embed-responsive-item" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Vv6DlAS4duM?si=ghmPI69R9bsOjH3Y" title="YouTube video player" width="560"></iframe></div>

<p style="margin: 1em 0px"><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="6ec5d502-f8c6-4907-8a48-15d2096519f0" href="/drugs/information-consumers-and-patients-drugs/transcript-how-does-fda-approve-new-drugs" title="How does the FDA approve new drugs?">Transcript</a></p>

<hr /><h2>What does the FDA do after drugs are approved?</h2>

<p>Based on real-time information we receive from patients, drug manufacturers, and healthcare professionals, we may make recommendations to update the drug labeling. </p>

<div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9"><iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" class="embed-responsive-item" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BW3nqkIqQOE?si=YcTdF6in142QL68n" title="YouTube video player" width="560"></iframe></div>

<p style="margin: 1em 0px"><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="8de305cb-6370-431f-9414-675d6906b772" href="/drugs/information-consumers-and-patients-drugs/transcript-what-does-fda-do-after-drugs-are-approved" title="What does the FDA do after drugs are approved?">Transcript</a></p>
</div>


